WHEREAS, FLEC is one of the electric cooperatives that deliver power to seventy-two
percent of Tennessee's landmass at rates thirty-seven percent below the national average; and
WHEREAS, FLEC currently serves portions of three counties (Blount, Loudon, and
Monroe) in Tennessee and has grown from serving 364 members with thirty miles of electric
lines in 1941 to serving more than 36,350 members over 3,100 miles of distribution lines today;
and
WHEREAS, growing with the area it serves so tirelessly, FLEC now has a 750 square-
mile service territory that includes a small portion of the Great Smoky Mountains National Park
and the Cherokee National Forest in combination with the beauty associated with the shorelines
of portions of the Fort Loudoun and Tellico reservoirs established by TVA to help meet the
energy and economic growth needs of the area; now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES OF THE ONE HUNDRED
FOURTEENTH GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE SENATE
CONCURRING, that we recognize and honor Fort Loudoun Electric Cooperative on the
occasion of its eighty-fifth anniversary and thank its board of directors, management, and
employees for their ongoing commitment to providing quality electric service at low rates to its
members in East Tennessee.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that an appropriate copy of this resolution be prepared
for presentation with this final clause omitted from such copy and upon proper request made to
the appropriate clerk, the language appearing immediately following the State seal appear
without House or Senate designation.
